					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment.</support>
								<extent>64 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>230</height>
										<width>190</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>150</height>
										<width>120</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>64 folios (+ one unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and one at the end; there are two systems of foliation, one running from left to right and one running from right to left. The references according to the one from right to left.)</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p> 	9 quires: i8 (folios 1-8), ii8 (folios 9-16), iii2 (folios 17-18), iv-viii8 (folios 19-58), ix6 (folios 59-64).</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="6 20" writtenLines="6 20">
									<p>Ruling is visible. </p>
									<p>Hair-side and flesh-side of the folios are not distinguishable.
</p>
									<p>Watermark on folio [i recto] and [65r], of a hexagonal star, unidentified.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square script, main text punctuated, captions and instructions for the Seder not punctuated.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>A handwritten note on paper, stuck onto the inside lower cover: <q>Le pitture rappresentareo I fatti principali delle Genesi e dell'Estudo fino al passaggio del Mar Rosso compito; li ultimi tre se referiscono ni riti Pasquali Ebraici, e il tuto alla fine del MS. contiene il Rituale della Pasqua delgi Ebrei.</q>
							</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Vergane Pietro</name>: inscribed with his name in pencil (folio <locus n="1r"/>).</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
